"Project: LuminaWeb - A networked bioluminescent invertebrate communication system. Utilizing genetically modified jellyfish and other deep-sea invertebrates, trained to react to environmental stimuli (sound, light, movement) and transmit data via controlled bioluminescence. The data is then processed and displayed as dynamic, interactive light patterns – think living, breathing digital art installations. We can even incorporate biofeedback – the invertebrates' responses directly mirroring human emotional states via wearable sensors! Imagine a concert where the music dictates the light, and the audience's mood influences the patterns! It's… ink-credible!"